The Commission of inquiry into state capture will hear the testimony of Director of BNP Capital, Daniel Mahlangu on Thursday. JOHANNESBURG - The commission of inquiry into state capture will hear the testimony of Director of BNP Capital, Daniel Mahlangu on Thursday. BNP Capital was the company Dudu Myeni wanted appointed to secure a loan for SAA. The Commission will also hear aviation related testimony of Former General Manager Human Capital (HR) South African Airways,  Mathulwane Mpshe. READ: SARS sets up secret inquiry to investigate Bosasa's tax affairs On Wednesday, the inquiry heard testimony from former SAA CEO, Sizakele Mzimela. Mzimela described how the former Public Enterprises Minister Malusi Gigaba was silent while his advisor gave her a tongue-lashing during a meeting concerning the Johannesburg-Mumbai route.